---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Baijiu vs Vodka: Why Clear Does Not Mean Similar';
const description = 'Baijiu and vodka can both be clear and strong, but they differ in fermentation, aroma, flavor, serving culture, and cocktail behavior.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <header class="article-header"><div class="narrow"><p class="eyebrow">Comparison</p><h1>Baijiu vs Vodka</h1><p class="lede">The fastest way to misunderstand baijiu is to call it Chinese vodka and stop thinking.</p></div></header>
  <section class="content"><article>
    <h2>The Similarity Is Mostly Visual</h2><p>Both spirits can be clear and high proof. After that, the comparison starts to break down. Vodka is usually designed around neutrality. Baijiu is built around aroma.</p>
    <h2>Fermentation Changes Everything</h2><p>Baijiu fermentation uses qu, grain, pits, jars, and microbial environments that create dense aroma compounds before distillation. That is why baijiu can smell fruity, savory, earthy, floral, or sauce-like.</p>
    <h2>How They Drink Differently</h2><p>Vodka often disappears into cocktails or is served chilled. Baijiu is usually served at room temperature in small cups, often with food and toasts. Its flavor is meant to be noticed.</p>
    <div class="callout">If vodka is often about clean structure, baijiu is about fermented aroma and social context.</div>
  </article></section>
</BaseLayout>
